      "doi": "arXiv:1606.04671",
      "kind": "baseline",
      "what_changed": "CompoNet composes previous modules at the output (policy) level via attention; ProgressiveNet connects all hidden layers of all previous columns to each new column via lateral connections.",
      "why": "Output-level composition yields linear O(n) parameter growth vs quadratic O(n²) in ProgressiveNet; avoids the hidden-layer coupling that causes quadratic growth.",
