    "insights": [
      "If a new module has direct access to the output probability vectors of all previous modules (rather than their hidden activations), it can use attention mechanisms conditioned on the current state to (a) selectively imitate the best previous policy, (b) learn a function over previous policies, or (c) ignore all previous outputs and learn from scratch — all without a dedicated composer and with only a constant-sized module per task."
